# Purpleweb Data Flow

Purpleweb (`src/lib/purpleweb/`) is the local-first runtime for page-visible Nostr event data. It sits above Dexie and delegates relay I/O to `$lib/nostr/service.js`.

## Rules (where purpleweb is adopted)

- Page-visible event data on purpleweb-owned surfaces must be read from Dexie through purpleweb. Routes and components must not display relay responses directly.
- All relay results must be written to Dexie first (`putEvents`). UI updates come from Dexie `liveQuery` / purpleweb reactive state.
- Consumers describe the model or addressable root they need (e.g. app, stack social root) — not relay filters, hydration toggles, or subscription lifecycles.
- SSR seed data is bootstrap input only; client-side display must converge immediately to Dexie-backed purpleweb state.
- Route code may publish user actions (comments, zaps); published events must be persisted to Dexie and read back through purpleweb or Dexie-derived local state.

## Ownership boundaries

| Concern | Owner |
|---------|-------|
| App detail reads + hydration | purpleweb (`createAppDetailQuery`) |
| App/stack social reads + hydration | purpleweb (`createAppSocialQuery`, `createStackSocialQuery`) |
| Catalog persistent subscriptions (apps, releases, stacks) | `$lib/nostr/service.js` via `+layout.svelte` |
| Catalog listing queries + load-more | `$lib/stores/nostr.svelte.js`, `stacks.svelte.js` |
| Stack detail entity + app resolution | Route code (not yet purpleweb) — same Dexie-first invariants apply |

When adding new page data on catalog detail or social surfaces, use or extend purpleweb. When touching listings or the app-shell relay pool, follow existing nostr/store patterns until those surfaces migrate.
